{
  "question_text": "<h3>Design Hit Counter</h3><p>Count hits in the last 5 minutes (300 seconds).</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "Operations (hit(t), getHits(t)).",
  "output_format": "Int counts.",
  "constraints": [
    "t is strictly increasing",
    "timestamps up to 10^9"
  ],
  "explanation": "Use a queue to store hits and remove old hits (> 300s) on getHits. Or use a fixed-size array (300) with counts.",
  "answer": "class HitCounter:\n    def __init__(self): self.hits = collections.deque()\n    def hit(self, t): self.hits.append(t)\n    def getHits(self, t):\n        while self.hits and self.hits[0] <= t - 300: self.hits.popleft()\n        return len(self.hits)",
